l guild26 (no space) and see what pops up.<br>
<br>
Each guild is given a sequential number as it's formed. When a guild officially disbands, its number becomes available for use again (so you'll see some newish guilds in some of the lower number ranges). If you do a /who all guild1 through /who all guild30, you should spot the League in there somewhere, as well as some of the older ones who are still around (of course, if no members of that guild are online, you won't see anything).<br>
<br>
Conclave of the Damned and Fire and Fury were both formed before the League, as I recall. Guild1 is Firiona's Chosen (the GM's). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kazanti>Kazanti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/1/03 7:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4898.topic&index=30>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Seeking a history of the League of Shadows</span><hr size=1> Gray was quite active after taking over leadership in helping me try and form the Confederation of Darkness (later to fall apart).  I have kept a lot of the old records and it did show a number of mergers, I believe 3 or 4 to LoS and dates should be close.  Link = <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/bconfederationofdarkness">pub44.ezboard.com/bconfed...ofdarkness</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
